1
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:08,560
[Scully's Voice]
For the first time...

2
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:11,640
I feel time
like a heartbeat,

3
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:16,080
the seconds pumping in my breast
like a reckoning,

4
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:20,640
the numinous mysteries that once
seemed so distant and unreal...

5
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:23,480
threatening clarity
in the presence of a truth...

6
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:26,120
entertained not in youth,

7
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:28,760
but only in its passage.

8
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:31,200
I feel these words
as if their meaning...

9
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:34,320
were weight
being lifted from me,

10
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:37,200
knowing that you will read them
and share my burden...

11
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:40,000
as I have come to trust
no other.

12
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,280
That you should know
my heart,

13
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:44,320
look into it,

14
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:48,880
finding there the memory
and experience that belong to you,

15
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:50,840
that are you,

16
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:55,480
is a comfort to me now
as I feel the tethers loose...

17
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:57,480
and the prospects darken...

18
00:00:57,560 --> 00:01:02,160
for the continuance of a journey
that began not so long ago,

19
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:06,000
and which began again with a faith
shaken and strengthened...

20
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:08,240
by your convictions.

21
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:12,440
If not for which I might never
have been so strong now...

22
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:17,080
as I cross to face you
and look at you incomplete,

23
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:20,000
hoping that you
will forgive me...

24
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:23,280
for not making the rest
of the journey with you.

25
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:19,440
Oncology ?

26
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:21,440
Thanks.

27
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:32,120
Scully ?

28
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,760
I, uh--

29
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:40,200
I stole these from some guy
with a broken leg down the hall.

30
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:44,000
He won't be able
to catch me.

31
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:46,640
How you doing ?

32
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:49,920
I guess that's the question.

33
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,640
Actually, I feel fine.

34
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:54,760
Good.

35
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:02,200
What, uh, exactly
are we lookin' at here ?

36
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:06,360
It's what's called
a naso-pharyngeal mass.

37
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:08,400
It's a small growth
on the wall...

38
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:11,320
between the Superior concha
and the Sphenoidal sinus.

39
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:14,800
- A growth ?
- A tumor.

40
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:20,440
You're the only one
I've called.

41
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:25,600
Okay. Is it operable ?

42
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:29,720
- No.
- But it's treatable.

43
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:34,080
The truth is that the type
and placement of the tumor...

44
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:37,400
make it difficult--
to the extreme.

45
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:42,040
I refuse to believe that.
I-l--

46
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:45,720
For all the times
I have said that to you,

47
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:49,080
I am as certain about this
as you have ever been.

48
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:54,120
I have cancer.

49
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:58,360
It is a mass on the wall
between my sinus and cerebrum.

50
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:03,320
If it pushes into my brain,
statistically there is about
zero chance of survival.

51
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:09,440
I don't accept that.
Th-There must be some people...

52
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,840
who have received treatment
for this who we can--

53
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:17,040
Yes, there are.

54
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:19,040
[ Sighs ]

55
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,960
This news comes as the worst
kind of surprise, Agent Scully.

56
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:31,480
I'm very sorry.

57
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:33,560
Thank you, sir.
I don't mean for this to be awkward,

58
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,520
and I would appreciate it if
we could keep this confidential.

59
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:39,720
I understand. I assume you’ll
be taking a leave of absence.

60
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:43,080
No, sir. I've asked my doctors
to hold on to my medical records...

61
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:46,800
until Agent Mulder and I can exhaust
a possible avenue of investigation.

62
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:50,080
- Investigation ?
- Last year Agent Scully and l...

63
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:52,920
pursued a case in which a number
of women, purported abductees,

64
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,800
experienced similar symptoms
after having implants removed
from the base of their necks.

65
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,880
A woman in Allen town,
Pennsylvania...

66
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:02,600
named Betsy Hagopian, was undergoing
treatment for naso-pharyngeal tumor.

67
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:05,280
We haven't been able
to contact her yet.

68
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:08,480
I'm sure you’re aware we have contacts
with the best physicians in the country.

69
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,520
Yes, sir.
But for my own reasons,

70
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,520
I would like to pursue this
through the Justice Department,

71
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:16,040
rather than as
a personal matter.

72
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,240
I'm sorry. No early birds.

73
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:44,680
We're not here for the garage sale.
We're looking for Betsy Hagopian.

74
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:47,200
- No one's returning our messages.
-Sorry.

75
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:50,440
Um,
Betsy's passed away.

76
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:53,360
Just two-and-a-half weeks ago.
Are you a relation ?

77
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,960
No. We're with the FBI.

78
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:59,400
- Been some kind of trouble ?
- Betsy was part of a Mufon Group.

79
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:01,800
I don't know.
I'm just the realtor.

80
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:05,160
Do you mind if we come inside
and take a look ?

81
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,640
Hey, Scully.

82
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:36,920
- Listen to this.
- [ Static Sounds ]

83
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:40,000
There are two lines coming in.
I noticed this one was lit.

84
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:42,440
Somebody's sending a fax
or a computer modem.

85
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:45,160
But who ?
And to send what ?

86
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:03,160
Somebody must have
remote access to the system.

87
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,040
They're downloading data.

88
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:10,400
Copying files. Let's get a trace
on them before whoever it is hangs up.

89
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:12,880
[Dialing Tone]

90
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:20,400
[ Scully]
Apartment 234
is listed under Kurt Crawford.

91
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,280
I'm gonna check around back.
See if you can get the manager.

92
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:10,360
Stop ! Federal agent !

93
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,120
Hold it !

94
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,080
[Scully]
put your hands where we can see them !

95
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:18,840
Is your name
Kurt Crawford ?

96
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:21,000
Yes.

97
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,440
- Scully ?
- What ?

98
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:34,560
I'm fine, Mulder.

99
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:39,280
Quit staring at me.
I'm fine.

100
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,240
-[Knocking At Door]
-[Mulder] You okay, Scully ?

101
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,800
Yeah. I'm just washing up.

102
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,680
[Scully]
You took his cuffs off.

103
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:13,120
He says he's a member of the same U.F.O.
Network Betsy Hagopian belonged to.

104
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:16,440
That he was downloading
files for safekeeping,
as Betsy had instructed him.

105
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:19,040
- Then why did he run ?
- He thinks his life's in danger.

106
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:23,320
He thinks there’s government
conspiracy to suppress the
information in those files.

107
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,120
- You think he's credible ?
- He seems to know a lot...

108
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,160
about what happened to Betsy
and the other women...

109
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:30,480
in the Mufon Group that
you met at her house.

110
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:32,680
That will have
to be cross-checked.

111
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:37,880
- We can't.
- Why not ?

112
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,200
How did they die ?

113
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:55,360
Brain cancer.
All within the last year.

114
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,680
All of them ?

115
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:00,440
From the group you met,
there's only Penny Northern.

116
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,480
She's in the hospital,
and it doesn't look good.

117
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:08,000
What makes you think
this is a conspiracy,
that the government's involved ?

118
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:11,000
What makes you think
it isn't ?

119
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:14,000
Eleven women are abducted,

120
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,520
all with similar recollections
about the experience.

121
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:18,720
All developing
identical brain tumors,

122
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:20,800
and all refused state
or federal health care...

123
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:23,160
because of their insistence
of the facts.

124
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:25,400
And all dying within
the space of a year.

125
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:29,680
[ Whispering ]

126
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:33,920
- I want you to listen to me.
- About what ?

127
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,520
About what you won't admit to
yourself, what you’re denying.

128
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,640
- What am I denying ?
- Where your cancer came from.

129
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:43,480
- It doesn't matter.
- It does matter.

130
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:47,320
If what you have is a result
of your abduction, and that is
something the government knows,

131
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:50,120
- then those are facts that
should be brought to light.
- I don't know what happened.

132
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:54,280
I have no clear recollection,
and I don't think these
abductions are even abductions.

133
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,960
These women are dead.

134
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,280
No, they are not.

135
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:04,000
One woman isn't--
this Penny Northern.

136
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,160
Mm-hmm.

137
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:09,040
If you won't listen to me,
then you should go talk to her.

138
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:12,040
About what ?

139
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,800
What it feels like
to be dying of cancer ?

140
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:19,480
What it's like to know there is
absolutely nothing you can do about it ?

141
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:23,560
If that’s too hard for you,
then go as an investigator.

142
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:25,880
You have one remaining witness,
Agent Scully.

143
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:29,120
I'd think you’d want to know
what her story is.

144
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:49,000
Dana. Hello.

145
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:55,200
I-I'm sorry. Did somebody tell you
I was coming to see you ?

146
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:57,160
No.

147
00:11:58,360 --> 00:12:00,320
Then how did you know
it was me ?

148
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,800
I recognized you.

149
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,840
I told you when we met
last year.

150
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:10,240
I held you and comforted you
in the place... after the tests.

151
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:15,440
I'm sorry. I don't mean
to be insensitive, but, uh...

152
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:17,880
I don't share
those memories.

153
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:21,320
- It's all right.
- [ Clears Throat ]

154
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:26,800
I've come to ask you
some questions.

155
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:30,520
- About Dr. Scanlon ?
- No. Who's Dr. Scanlon ?

156
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:35,320
He's treating the cancer.
He treated Betsy too.

157
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,840
He thinks he might have
isolated the cause.

158
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,840
And that if
he'd caught it earlier,

159
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:47,160
he might have been able
to do more for her.

160
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:49,160
And for me.

161
00:12:58,160 --> 00:13:01,400
- His name's Scanlon ?
- Yes.

162
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,600
What did you want
to ask me ?

163
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:14,400
[Cell phone Ringing]

164
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,920
- Mulder.
- [ Scully] Mulder, it's me.

165
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:21,000
- Where are you ?
- I'm at the hospital
with Penny Northern.

166
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:23,280
- Where are you ?
- I'm at Betsy Hagopian's...

167
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:26,280
going through some hard files
before stuff starts disappearing.

168
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:28,720
Call me an early bird, but
I think I've found something.

169
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:31,000
Some of these women who
have died, they're childless.

170
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:34,040
They've been treated for infertility
at a clinic 30 miles from here--

171
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,840
- Penny Northern and
Betsy Hagopian among them.
- Mulder, that's--

172
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:40,520
I've made phone calls,
tried to get some information,
but nobody is talking to me.

173
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:43,040
Mulder, I need you
to come up here.

174
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:46,040
Did you find
something there ?

175
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:49,320
I need you to bring the overnight bag
from the trunk of the car.

176
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,360
And I need you
to call my mother...

177
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:53,640
and ask her to bring
some things up to the hospital.

178
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:55,680
Is there anything
I should know ?

179
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,880
Mulder, whatever
you found,

180
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:00,600
or whatever
you might find,

181
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:04,120
I think we both know that...

182
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:07,640
right now
the truth is in me.

183
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:11,720
And that's where
I need to pursue it...

184
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,880
as soon as possible.

185
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:17,760
I will be right there.

186
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:13,280
[Door Opens,
Closes]

187
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:15,320
Agent Mulder ?

188
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:20,520
Agent Mulder ?

189
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:23,400
Dana ? I'm Dr. Scanlon.

190
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:26,920
We spoke last night
on the phone.

191
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:29,080
Yeah. Hi. Sorry.

192
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,400
I was sleeping.

193
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:34,960
I noticed.

194
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:37,000
How's your energy level,
generally ?

195
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:40,040
Oh, you know, l--

196
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:43,800
I don't--
I don't feel sick at all.

197
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:46,440
Your M.R.I.'s and your charts
aren't here yet.

198
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,640
But I have an idea
what to expect.

199
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:51,320
You probably do too,
from your medical training.

200
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:54,960
I know that chemotherapy
is going to make me sick.

201
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:57,520
And the radiation.

202
00:16:57,600 --> 00:17:00,840
They're both part of a high-dose
approach to knock your system down...

203
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:04,880
so that we can attempt
a gene therapy on p-53.

204
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:09,240
You're gonna feel
like dying.

205
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:15,880
- Dana.
- Hi, Mom.

206
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:18,840
Hi.

207
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,640
This is Dr. Scanlon.

208
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:25,480
- Hi.
- Hi.

209
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:28,720
I, uh-- I drove.

210
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:31,920
I was gonna take the shuttle,
but it's only an hour more by car.

211
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:36,200
- Can you imagine ?
- Mom ?

212
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:38,560
I'm fine.
I'm going to be fine.

213
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,960
I'm just here
for treatment.

214
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:43,000
I'm gonna go.

215
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:46,800
I've ordered additional blood work.
I'd like to start this afternoon.

216
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:49,240
Thank you.

217
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,040
Mom, I know what
you're going to say,

218
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:56,840
but I don't have any experience
being sick.

219
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,080
I promise you,
I feel fine.

220
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:04,120
I feel--
[ Sighs ]

221
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:08,160
I don't know why
you didn't tell me.

222
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:14,000
I don't know why you
didn't tell me immediately !

223
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:20,360
I wanted to get
all the answers first.

224
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,840
And you found them
here ?

225
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,320
I have found some clarity.

226
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:37,360
And maybe a way
to fight back.

227
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:43,200
I don't want to be kept
in the dark.

228
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:47,520
You'll know, Mom.

229
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:57,560
[ Crying ]

230
00:18:57,640 --> 00:19:01,240
You have always been
the strong one.

231
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:07,320
[ Sobbing ]
But you’re my only daughter now.

232
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,960
I know.

233
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:17,640
[ Sobbing
Oh, Dana.

234
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:24,040
[Scully's Voice]
In med school,

235
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:27,800
I learned that cancer arrives
in the body unannounced--

236
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:31,920
a dark stranger
who takes up residence,

237
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:35,640
turning its new home
against itself.

238
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:40,240
This is the evil of cancer---

239
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,600
that it starts as an invader,

240
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,800
but soon becomes one
with the invaded,

241
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:48,440
forcing you to destroy it.

242
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:51,160
But only at the risk
of destroying yourself.

243
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,280
[ Whirring ]

244
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:58,200
It is science's
demon possession.

245
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:02,680
My treatments--
science's attempt at exorcism.

246
00:20:05,360 --> 00:20:07,280
Mulder, I hope
that in these terms...

247
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:11,440
you might know it
and know me,

248
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:13,680
and accept this stranger
so many recognize...

249
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:17,240
but cannot ever completely
cast out.

250
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:24,520
And if the darkness should have
swallowed me as you read this,

251
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:29,720
you must never think
there was the possibility
of some secret intervention--

252
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,840
something you might have done.

253
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:36,800
And though we have traveled
far together,

254
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:41,320
this last distance must necessarily
be traveled alone.

255
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:08,200
[Door Opens,
Closes]

256
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:23,000
I've got a gun pointed at your head.
Turn around very slowly.

257
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:33,400
Kurt Crawford. We seem to be traveling
in the same circles these days.

258
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:34,920
Put the gun away.

259
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,320
You disappeared with those files
from Betsy Hagopian's.

260
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:40,000
I called you half a dozen times.
I got to thinking you were a liar.

261
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:43,520
- Tell me I'm wrong.
- I'm looking for the same thing
that you are.

262
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:47,360
I've been trying to hack into
that system, but I can't seem
to make it past the password.

263
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:51,080
- You think you can
get access from here ?
- I need to find that password.

264
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:10,880
"Vegreville."

265
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:22,520
- We're in.
- Huh.

266
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:38,440
[penny]
Dana ? Dana, it's okay.

267
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:43,280
It's okay, Dana.
You'll be okay.

268
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:54,880
[ Whispering ]
Where am I ?

269
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:58,440
You're in your own bed now.
You're safe.

270
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:02,520
I feel nauseous.

271
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:06,600
It's the chemo.
The chemo was always the worst.

272
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:14,600
I had a bad dream.
Some--

273
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:21,160
Someone was doing
something bad to me.

274
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:24,480
[ Sighs ]

275
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:30,560
Mmm. You were there.
I heard your voice.

276
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:34,480
They let me come to you
during the procedures.

277
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:37,720
- [ Moans Softly]
- I don't know why.

278
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,560
Human compassion is
not something that they have.

279
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:42,560
I'm sorry, Penny.

280
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:46,040
I can't--

281
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,760
I can't hear this
right now.

282
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:55,600
You've got to try
and make sense of it, Dana.

283
00:23:57,280 --> 00:24:00,920
It'll help you
through the pain.

284
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:04,040
To understand
why this is--

285
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:06,080
this is happening to you.

286
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:22,840
I need you to set up
a meeting for me.

287
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:30,840
Hold all my calls.

288
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,880
Where's Agent Scully ?

289
00:24:32,920 --> 00:24:36,320
She's in a hospital in Allentown
beginning treatment.

290
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:38,480
What happened to
your investigative avenues ?

291
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:40,680
They've taken a turn.

292
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:43,120
A pretty big U-turn,
by the looks of it.

293
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:46,440
This is a file directory from
a federally-operated fertility clinic.

294
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:48,680
Agent Scully's name
is on this file.

295
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:52,520
Although I'm pretty damn
sure she's never undergone
treatment for infertility.

296
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:55,400
- What's in the file ?
- I don't know.
It’s just a directory...

297
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:58,200
for a mainframe housed
in the Lombard Research Facility.

298
00:24:58,240 --> 00:25:00,800
So you want to set up
a meeting. With whom ?

299
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:05,840
The Cigarette Man.

300
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:08,280
I have no doubt in my mind
he's behind this.

301
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:11,640
- You've come to me
before like this, Mulder.
- Well, this is different.

302
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:13,640
- I'm willing to deal now.
- Find another way.

303
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:15,880
No. No !
I need that meeting.

304
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:19,320
You deal with this man, you offer him
anything, and he will own you forever.

305
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:21,320
He knows what they did
to Agent Scully !

306
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,560
He may know how
to save her !

307
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:27,040
If he knows, you can know too,
but you can't ask the truth
of a man who trades in lies.

308
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:31,320
- I won't let you.
- We are talking about
Agent Scully's life.

309
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,720
Find another way.

310
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:42,840
[Frohike]
The Lombard System
is a dedicated mainframe...

311
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:45,560
impossible to hack,
so they say.

312
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:48,600
- How'd you guys get in ?
- A modified Clipper Chip
we cannibalized...

313
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:51,240
from a government surplus
Army Field Encoder.

314
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:53,360
We bought it back
from the Chinese.

315
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:56,160
But for all the work
it took to get in,

316
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:59,880
what we got on Agent Scully's file, we
don't know how much help it's gonna be.

317
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:02,760
- What do you mean ?
- It's a gene code we've seen before.

318
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:07,400
- Detected in Scully's blood
after her abduction.
- Does it tell us anything ?

319
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:10,440
Normal DNA is inactive
when in its helical form.

320
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:13,240
When it's unwound,
or branched like this one,

321
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:16,840
- that's when it's active,
when it can mutate.
- It's what made her sick.

322
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:19,920
Why store something like this,
and why keep it a secret ?

323
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:22,360
Scientists get funky about
having their research poached.

324
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:25,120
Somebody might be trying
to find a cause.

325
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:28,200
- Or a cure.
- Theoretically.

326
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:31,920
You guys ever been to
the Lombard Research Facility?

327
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:38,160
Well, pick out something black and sexy
and prepare to do some funky poaching.

328
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:47,520
[ Sighs ]

329
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:53,320
It's funny. I always thought
of you as Fox Mulder's patron.

330
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,480
You'd think
under your aegis,

331
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:59,800
he wouldn't be consigned
to a corner of the basement.

332
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:02,560
At least he doesn't take
an elevator up to get to work.

333
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:05,000
You think I'm the devil,
Mr. Skinner ?

334
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:07,160
I'm not here to talk about
what I think about you.

335
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:10,120
Then why are you here ?

336
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,200
Is it Mulder's partner
and her illness ?

337
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:18,880
Is it terminal ?
Is it cancer ?

338
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:21,040
You tell me.

339
00:27:21,080 --> 00:27:25,560
Modern medicine today--
I hear they can perform miracles.

340
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:33,800
I need a miracle.

341
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:38,920
Well, you think a lot more
of me than you let on, Mr. Skinner.

342
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:42,120
- What'll it take ?
- For Agent Scully's life ?

343
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:47,000
- What would you offer ?
- What'll it take ?

344
00:27:49,040 --> 00:27:50,960
Well,

345
00:27:56,920 --> 00:28:00,720
I'll have to get back
to you on that.

346
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:06,240
Oh, Mr. Skinner.

347
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:08,560
Which way is the elevator ?

348
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:42,160
He'll double back
in 54 seconds.

349
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:46,800
Frohike,
where are you guys ?

350
00:28:46,840 --> 00:28:48,840
We're in the K-section
of the storm drain...

351
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:51,920
where the communications system
links up to public power.

352
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:54,920
Stand by.

353
00:28:58,280 --> 00:29:00,840
Two minutes
for a systems check.

354
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:05,360
We got to go.

355
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:07,360
We're in motion.

356
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:20,160
They're in.

357
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:23,520
Security camera's off-line,
patching in now.

358
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:26,400
[Frohike]
Smile, Byers. You're on Candid Camera.

359
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:29,160
Exterior security
has been breached.

360
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,360
Langly,
are you reading this ?

361
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:54,400
Redundant systems-- triple-shut bypass.
This is a toughie.

362
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:57,640
You guys couldn't spring
for two of these ? What is going on ?

363
00:29:57,720 --> 00:30:00,200
Mulder, this is
gonna take a moment.

364
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:13,480
[Mulder]
Boys, we have a problem.

365
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:15,680
The doctor treating Scully's cancer
is on staff here.

366
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:19,920
More mysteries await.
Bypass is complete.

367
00:30:21,480 --> 00:30:24,880
I need someone to get to Scully
to stop treatment.

368
00:30:24,960 --> 00:30:26,880
Right now, you're the only one
who can do that.

369
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:33,080
[Scully's Voice] I have not written
to you in thelast24hours...

370
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:37,880
because the treatment has weakened
my spirit as well as my body.

371
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:42,040
Mulder, it's difficult to describe
to you the fear of facing an enemy...

372
00:30:42,120 --> 00:30:45,400
which I can neither conquer
nor escape.

373
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:48,480
penny Northern
has taken a downturn.

374
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:51,960
I now look at her with a respect
that can only come from one...

375
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:55,360
who is about to walk
the same dark path.

376
00:30:55,480 --> 00:31:00,240
Seeing her, I can't help but
see myself in a month or a year.

377
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:04,760
I pray that I have her courage
to face this journey.

378
00:31:04,840 --> 00:31:07,240
Mulder, I feel you close...

379
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:10,560
though I know you are now
pursuing your own path.

380
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:13,200
For that I am grateful--

381
00:31:13,280 --> 00:31:16,000
more than
I could ever express.

382
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:20,920
I need to know you are out there
if I am ever to see through this.

383
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:22,960
Langly, where the hell
am I going ?

384
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:25,160
We're losing you
on the video feed, Mulder.

385
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:28,280
Mulder ? Did you
do anything, Frohike ?

386
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:30,320
Nada.
I didn't touch a thing.

387
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:37,520
[police Car Radio,
indistinct]

388
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:41,840
Down here.

389
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:47,080
- Langly, can you hear me ?
- [ Radio Transmission Scrambled ]

390
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:50,120
Langly, I can't hear you.

391
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:54,120
Langly, I can't hear you.

392
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:56,280
- [ Knocking ]
- Open the door.

393
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:07,160
Open the damn door !

394
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:17,840
Agent Mulder, come in.

395
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:35,240
- You're hybrids.
- Please come in
so that we might explain.

396
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:06,040
[ Water Bubbling ]

397
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:09,680
- You've been using me.
- Not at all.

398
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:12,760
You're arrival was only coincident
with the execution of our objective.

399
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:15,560
- What objective ?
-[Kurt#2] To subvert the project.

400
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:31,920
The project
that created us.

401
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:34,400
I've seen this boy before.

402
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:39,600
These boys are you.

403
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:42,040
We're among
the end result.

404
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:45,680
- And you want to destroy them ?
- No!

405
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:57,120
What we want is
the same thing that you want.

406
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:59,280
What are these ?

407
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:07,520
Human ova.

408
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:21,760
Taken from whom ?

409
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:24,880
What ?

410
00:34:24,960 --> 00:34:28,640
Harvested during her abduction
through a high-amplification
radiation procedure...

411
00:34:28,720 --> 00:34:31,360
that caused...
super-ovulation.

412
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:36,280
- Why ?
- For fertilization.

413
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:41,520
They constitute one half of
the necessary raw materials.

414
00:34:43,160 --> 00:34:45,160
For genetic hybridization.

415
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:48,960
For reproduction.

416
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:53,360
These women--

417
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:55,400
These women
are your birth mothers.

418
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:57,920
Barren now...

419
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,040
from the same procedure
that caused their cancer.

420
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:04,520
And now
they're left to die,

421
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:08,200
their condition hastened
by the man running this project.

422
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:28,960
- You're trying to save them.
- They're our mothers.

423
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:30,960
[ Langly On Radio ]
Mulder, are you there ? Do you copy ?

424
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:34,440
Langly, I can't hear you.

425
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:36,440
You've got a security breach
in sectionJ-1 4.

426
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:39,360
- [ Mulder] You sure it's not Byers ?
- Nope.

427
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:06,000
I've got Byers right here
on my screen.

428
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:08,840
[ Mulder] Langly, help me out.
I don't know where I'm goin'.

429
00:36:08,880 --> 00:36:11,240
You're in a bio-quarantine wing
leading to an exit.

430
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:13,240
[ Langly] At the end of the hall,
you'll access a door
to a bio-secure room.

431
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:20,320
I'm working
on the locks now.

432
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:23,240
Okay, Langly, Frohike,
I'm here. Open the door.

433
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:32,200
The doors work under redundant
systems. We're working fast.

434
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:35,200
Work faster !

435
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:43,480
[ Gunshots ]

436
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:46,280
Langly, open the door now !

437
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:51,280
[ Gunshots ]

438
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:59,200
Get me out !

439
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:05,840
- Get me out of here now !
- Almost there.

440
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:54,720
Go !

441
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:57,040
Nurse. Nurse !

442
00:37:57,120 --> 00:37:59,040
Dana Scully's supposed to be
in her room. Where is she ?

443
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:01,480
- She's not there ?
- No. What happened to her ?

444
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:03,960
- I don't know. I--
- Who the hell does know ?

445
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:06,720
Mulder!

446
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,760
- What happened to Scully ?
- I got to her.

447
00:38:24,520 --> 00:38:27,480
Where is she now?

448
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:33,280
Dr. Scanlon
isn't coming back ?

449
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:39,360
No. I don't think so,
Penny.

450
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,760
Dana, I want you to get well.

451
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:48,720
You've been such a comfort.

452
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:51,600
You've got to be the one.

453
00:38:52,760 --> 00:38:54,920
You can't give up hope.

454
00:38:56,720 --> 00:38:59,320
I haven't.

455
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:38,520
I won't.

456
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:45,720
Is she gone ?

457
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,960
I'm sorry.

458
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:56,120
I know
what she meant to you.

459
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:58,480
When I came to find you
and you weren't in your room,

460
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:03,160
I got scared
that something had happened.

461
00:40:03,240 --> 00:40:05,400
And I read some
of what you wrote.

462
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,720
[ Sighs ]

463
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:16,360
I didn't want you
to read that.

464
00:40:16,480 --> 00:40:19,080
I had decided
to throw it out.

465
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:25,240
I decided tonight
that, um--

466
00:40:27,120 --> 00:40:31,200
that I'm not gonna let
this thing beat me.

467
00:40:31,280 --> 00:40:33,800
I came into this hospital
able to work.

468
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:43,400
And that's how I'm leaving.

469
00:40:43,520 --> 00:40:47,160
- Byers tell you about Dr. Scanlon ?
- Yes.

470
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:50,720
He may very well
have killed those women.

471
00:40:50,800 --> 00:40:53,160
That will have to be proven--
if we find him.

472
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:56,800
When we find him.

473
00:40:56,880 --> 00:41:00,680
Something was done to you-- something
you’re just beginning to remember.

474
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:04,960
You can't quite figure it out,
but it can be explained,
and it will be explained.

475
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:08,960
And no matter what you think
as a scientist or doctor,

476
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:11,640
there is a way
and you will find it...

477
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:14,080
to save yourself.

478
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:17,400
[ Sighs ]

479
00:41:17,520 --> 00:41:19,880
Mulder, I can't kid myself.

480
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:23,800
People live with cancer.

481
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:29,640
They carry on.
And so will l.

482
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:33,720
You know,
I've got things to finish...

483
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:40,280
to prove to myself,
to my family.

484
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:48,320
But for my own reasons.

485
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:06,920
Come on back.

486
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:10,280
The truth
